Church fire in Nantes, France: Parish volunteers admit to arson and silence - chinanews.com
Chinanews.com, July 26. According to foreign media reports, on July 18, the religious and historical architectural treasures of Nantes, France, and the famous Cathedral of St. Peter and St. Paul were severely damaged in a fire, and the large pipe organ was completely destroyed.
