Xinhua News Agency, Moscow, July 25. According to the plan of the Russian Ministry of Defense, the upgraded version of the Russian armed helicopter (hereinafter referred to as Wuzhi) Ka-52-Ka-52m will be completed for the first time in December this year. The model will be greatly improved in terms of reconnaissance, communications and weapon performance.
According to a recent report by the Russian "Yediot", the Wuzhika-52m is called the "Super Alligator". Its development contract was signed by the Russian military and military industrial units in April last year. At present, the first two of the upgraded version of Wuzhi are undergoing transformation and replacement at the Far East Helicopter Manufacturing Plant of the Russian "Progress" Aerospace Group. Its national-level testing and improvement will be completed by October 2022.
According to Russian experts who understand the above-mentioned upgrade work, the "predecessor" of the "super alligator" - Wuzhika-52 - was officially installed in November 2011. The model revealed some weaknesses in use. This renovation and upgrade is precisely to "make up for shortcomings".
According to the report, compared with the Ka-52, the Ka-52m will partially adopt new protective materials that will not increase weight. Its pilot cockpit will be reinforced and equipped with new equipment to resist missile attacks, thereby increasing the probability of battlefield survival; a more powerful generator will be assembled to power more complex airborne electronic equipment; the photoelectric system will be upgraded to detect and identify more distant battlefield targets; the new light multi-purpose missile equipped with major attack armored combat vehicles and reinforced concrete fortifications has a range of up to 20 kilometers, which is about double the range of similar missiles used by Russia's active armed forces; its defense weapons and communication equipment will be used as much as possible with the Mi-28NM armed helicopters that can attack air targets, making related maintenance simple and economical.
In addition, the Ka-52m will have more advanced electronic guidance systems, weapon targeting systems and navigation equipment.
Russian experts also said that it is worth noting that the Ka-52m will be equipped with communication equipment to communicate with drones, so as to obtain real-time information transmitted by nearby drones in the air, such as displaying images taken by drones on the cockpit screen of the helicopter.
According to the plan, the pilot of the Ka-52m can directly control the drones that cooperate with it, thereby improving the pilot's grasp of the battlefield situation and the guidance of long-range missiles.
According to Russian media reports, Russian Deputy Defense Minister Krivoruchko said in December last year that the Russian Ministry of Defense plans to purchase more than 110 Wuzhika-52Ms by 2027.
