"Plug up Jiangnan" to pursue the poetic "Yellow River Dream " - chinanews.com
(China's Poverty Reduction Story) "Put Jiangnan" in Pursuit of Poetic "Yellow River Dream"
China News Service, Yinchuan, July 26 (Yang Di) "Jiuqu Yellow River Wanli Sha, waves and waves ripple from the horizon."
The Yellow River, which has aroused the feelings of countless literati, has given birth to the beautiful and rich Ningxia Plain. Now, Ningxia, which has the reputation of "plugging up Jiangnan", is adhering to the concept of "ecological priority and green development" and pursuing the poetic "Yellow River Dream".
The "Bibo Dream" of Heqing Water Show
"The Yellow River in the world is rich in Ningxia", and the Yellow River flows through Ningxia for 397 kilometers, which is the "mother river" for raising one party.
However, with the rapid advancement of industrialization and urbanization, the development, utilization and management and protection of rivers and lakes are unbalanced, and chaos such as over-standard sewage discharge, lake reclamation, and encroachment on water areas have emerged, leading to black and smelly water bodies, excessive water quality, dirty environment, and ecological degradation.
Now, Ningxia is promoting the diverse restoration of water ecology and striving to return the Yellow River to Xiuhe Qing.
Water control must start at the source.
In Yinchuan, Ningxia, the local area adopted the method of "standard improvement + pollution control + strict management". All sewage from industrial parks have been treated centrally, all urban sewage treatment plants have achieved level I A standard discharge, and the black and smelly water bodies in urban built-up areas have been basically eliminated, and the third batch of Chinese black and smelly water demonstration cities has been successfully declared.
In addition, Ningxia fully implemented the river and lake long system in 2017, and now it has achieved full coverage of the five-level river and lake long responsibility system in districts, counties and villages, and the river and lake long patrol has become the norm.
The 64-year-old Gu Jincheng, who lives in a village by the Yellow River, witnessed the changes in the Yellow River: "The previous water had a bad smell, and after rectification, the smell was gone."
Gu Jincheng said that the ecological environment is better and his life is more comfortable. Now he often goes for a walk by the Yellow River with his family to feel the blue water and blue sky.
The "Wetland Dream" of Sagull Xiang Collection
Birds, green trees, plank roads, clear water... the beauty of the "sand gulls Xiang Collection" written by Fan Zhongyun has become a reality in the Yellow River Wetland Park in Yinchuan, Ningxia.
The Yellow River flows through Ningxia, forming a variety of wetlands such as river wetlands, lake wetlands, and swamp wetlands along the way, which plays an important role in promoting the rational use of water resources and water ecological balance, and has also become an important international bird migration channel.
Since 2009, relevant departments in Ningxia have invested a total of about 3.45 billion yuan in wetland protection projects. At present, Yinchuan Wetland covers an area of 19,200 hectares, with a wetland protection rate of 78.5%, and there are nearly 200 natural lakes and marsh wetlands. There are 5 national wetland parks, 1 national urban wetland park, 6 autonomous region-level wetland parks, and 8 municipal parks.
Lu Jinhu, deputy director of the Yinchuan Wetland Protection Center, told reporters that wetland protection has increased biodiversity, which is particularly evident in birds. "The gull is an endangered bird, with only more than 20,000 in the world, of which more than 2,000 live in Yinchuan Wetland."
At the same time, Ningxia has delineated a 500-meter red line for the wetland protection area on both sides of the Yinchuan section of the Yellow River in accordance with the law, stipulating that except for public welfare projects, no unit or individual may carry out development, construction and business activities within the scope of protection.
Zhao Shaoyong, deputy director of the Yinchuan Water Conservancy Service Center, introduced that through the treatment of the source of pollution, the comprehensive improvement of river and lake ecology, and the construction of terminal wetlands, the water quality of the nine main yellow drains in Ningxia has now reached 100% of the water level. "Now the water is clear, the fish are swimming, and the flowers are blooming."
The "Drinking Water Dream" of inclusive people's livelihood
Yinchuan City in Ningxia once had an "awkward" title: The only city along the Yellow River that "guarded the Yellow River for water and drink."
Since 2010, Yinchuan City has been facing a persistent shortage of water during the peak summer period. The "pain of water shortage" in the past ten years has become a painful summer experience for many high-floor residents. However, under the current situation that major water sources are at the limit of over-mining and a large area of groundwater over-exploitation funnel area has been formed under the urban underground, water-borne water shortage has become a difficult problem besetting Yinchuan City.
Thanks to the improvement of the water quality of the Yellow River, drinking purified Yellow River water has become a good way to solve the drinking water problems of local residents.
Ding Ming, deputy director of the Yinchuan Water Affairs Bureau, introduced that in order to improve the living and production water needs of urban and rural residents in Yinchuan, Ningxia launched the Yinchuan Metropolitan Area West Line Water Supply Project in due course, replacing the original underground water source with high-quality Yellow River water.
"On December 29, 2019, the water supply project officially opened water to the three districts of Yinchuan City. In 2020, residents of Minning Town and Helan County also drank the Yellow River water."
Ding Ming said that the Yinchuan Water Conservancy Department will comprehensively consider the transformation of the integration of regional rural drinking water and urban water supply. "In the next step, we will integrate all scattered rural water supply points into the Western Line water supply project, and it is expected that the integrated urban and rural water supply in Yinchuan region will be basically achieved by the end of this year."
