There were two memorial services on the first day.
On Saturday, at the public memorial service at Troy University in Alabama, five siblings and a nephew talked about Lewis as a loving and fearless family man.
Lewis' youngest brother, Henry "Grant" Lewis, said at the meeting: "He spent his lifetime to helpe others."
Samuel Lewis said that his mother had warned John "not to cause trouble, not to cause trouble."
He added that John did not heed his mother's warning, saying that "We all know that John always got into trouble and always getting into trouble, but that's because he insisted on the right thing, which was a good trouble."
Lewis' brothers and sisters reminded people at the memorial service that John's most famous argument was to create "good trouble", that is, as long as it is for justice, he does not shy away from provoking trouble.
John once applied to Troy University in Troy, Alabama, where he was born, but Troy University, an all-white school at the time, rejected his application for admission.
John Lewis, who preached the gospel to chickens on his farm as a child, eventually earned a degree in religion and philosophy from Fisk University.
Many years later, Troy University awarded Lewis an honorary doctorate.
Senator Doug Jones from Alabama said that the current protesters are "protesting peacefully and non-violently", just like Lewis did in the civil rights movement.
Jones said: "Even if President Trump knocked over a boat and described all the protesters as thugs, he was wrong.
The protesters are patriots, and they want the United States to move towards a more equal country. "
A series of six-day events to commemorate Lewis will culminate at a funeral in Georgia this week.
Lewis' coffin was parked at a public memorial service at Troy University on Saturday, and people came to pay tribute to the pioneer of the civil rights movement.
Later on Saturday, a private ceremony paid tribute to him in a small church in Selma, Alabama, followed by a public memorial service.
On Sunday, Lewis' body will pass through the Edmund Pettus Bridge in Selma.
In 1965, he and the demonstrators demanding the right to vote for blacks were severely beaten by the Alabama police in front of this bridge, and the police also threw tear gas at the demonstrators.
Lewis was almost killed at the time.
This day will later be called "Bloody Sunday".
Lewis' body will be transported to Montgomery, the capital of Alabama.
Mayor Steven Reed encouraged people to line up on the sidewalk to complete this final journey with Lewis.
At the same time, officials require the public to wear masks and maintain social distance when participating in activities.
Alabama Governor Kay Ivey ordered the flags to be lowered at half-mast on Saturday and Sunday in honor of Lewis.
During the nearly one-week commemoration, Lewis's body will be placed in the Alabama State Capitol in Montgomery, the Georgia State Capitol in Atlanta, and the U.S. Capitol in Washington for people to express their condolences.
U.S. House Speaker Nancy Pelosi and Senate Majority Leader Mitch McConnell announced last week that people can come to the U.S. Capitol on Monday and Tuesday to pay their respects to Lewis.
Due to the coronavirus, the public mourning will take place outdoors.
Shenzhen publicly solicited comments on the introduction of health regulations - Xinhuanet
Xinhua News Agency, Shenzhen, July 26 (Reporters Mao Siqian and Bai Yu) Encourage residents to do physical examinations frequently and detect problems early; prohibit the sale of alcoholic beverages to minors; establish an online game health review system; employers must be equipped with full-time and part-time health management personnel... The "Shenzhen Special Economic Zone Health Regulations (Draft for Comments)" was officially released a few days ago, and Shenzhen residents will have their own "health law".
In order to encourage residents to do physical examinations frequently and detect problems early, the above-mentioned draft for comments proposes that the health department should formulate a basic catalogue of health check-up items based on factors such as different ages and occupations.
The cost of health check-ups that fall within the scope of the basic catalogue of health check-up items shall be paid by the social medical insurance coordination fund at the standard of once per person per year.
The draft for comments makes it clear that employers should rationally allocate human resources, arrange staff working hours, and implement a rotation system for employees with heavy mental and physical workloads, so as to avoid excessive loss of human functions or physical and mental health damage to employees' health, and strictly implement the paid leave system for employees.
In addition, employers must be equipped with full-time and part-time health management personnel, and regularly organize and carry out employee health examinations.
In terms of the physical and mental health of minors, the draft for comments proposes that the sale of alcoholic beverages to minors is prohibited, and the sales location of alcoholic beverages is restricted. For violations of the regulations, the market supervision and management department will order corrections and impose a fine of 30,000 yuan.
In addition to "prohibition", minors should also "exercise more".
According to the requirements of the draft for comments, the school should arrange student sports activities for more than one hour every day.
For online games, public security, culture, radio, tourism, sports, network supervision, health department should improve the health supervision system of Internet service business premises, establish an online game health review system, and create a good communication space and communication culture for promoting the healthy growth of teenagers.
In addition, the draft for comments also proposed that influenza patients must wear masks when entering and leaving public places, and medical and health institutions fined 20,000 yuan for leaking patients' privacy without consent.
It is worth noting that, in addition to the physical and mental health of residents, the draft for comments also requires that various departments in Shenzhen should assess the impact of public policy implementation on the health of the population before formulating plans involving urban spatial planning and construction, industrial park planning and construction, resource development and utilization and ecological environment protection, and biomedical industry development, normative documents, and approving major construction projects and implementing major public service projects.
If it has not been assessed or will have a more serious adverse impact on urban public health or the health of residents, it shall not be formulated or approved for implementation.
