Yu'ebao's income went down "post-90s" but "retaliatory" to save money?
With the decline in Yu'ebao's earnings, not only did the "post-90s" not escape from the balance treasure, but began to "retaliate" to save money?
The "Yu'ebao Post-90s Savings Report" (2020 edition) recently released by the China New Economic Research Institute and Alipay shows that in the first half of the year, "post-90s" prefer to save money: The amount of money saved per capita increased by nearly 40% compared with 2019.
Interestingly, the "post-90s" tend to start with a small amount of "small money", and 60% of the average amount of money saved is less than 20 yuan...
Using the balance to save money has also become the "post-90s" habit of saving money.
Data shows that of the 700 million Yu'ebao users, 134 million are "post-90s".
China has 174 million "post-90s", that is to say, about 3 out of every 4 "post-90s" in the country are using the balance to save money.
At present, the 7-day annualized yield of money funds such as Yu'ebao has fallen to about 1.5% from a level above 2% at the beginning of the year.
Even so, it did not affect the pace of "post-90s" saving money.
In the context of the improvement of Yu'e Bao's "money saving effect", many young people who are used to using Yu'e Bao have also directly transformed into "basic people".
Alipay data shows that as of July 13, the number of new "basic people" on Alipay has more than doubled year-on-year in the past month, and more and more young people have achieved "advanced" financial management on Alipay.
Some analysts believe that the flow of funds from the balance treasure to the stock market is also an important reason for the clear decline in the share of money funds in June.
The report also shows that "post-90s" girls tend to save more money, on average 20% more than boys save; 60% of users who hold funds on the Alipay platform are men, and women tend to choose more robust financial management methods than men.
After saving money, what are the plans for the "post-90s"?
Alipay data shows that "post-90s" have the habit of saving money for their goals, and the most users use travel as a goal to save money.
Affected by the epidemic, many "post-90s" saved money to prepare for travel after the epidemic; the resumption of cinema operations also provided a new way to shift from saving money to consumption.
