The reporter learned at the meeting that vascular disease is the largest cause of death in China. The aorta, as the main channel of various organs of the human body, flows from the heart to the whole body and plays an important role.
The occurrence of aortic disease is often accompanied by high risk, high mortality, and high difficulty in treatment. The thickest section of the aorta is 4 cm in diameter. Once a hemangioma is formed, a rupture occurs, or the vascular intima ruptures to produce a dissection, it will cause massive bleeding, which is very dangerous.
In recent years, as people's lifestyles have changed and the pace of life has accelerated, China has become the world's largest country with hypertension, and aortic diseases have also increased. Today, with the development of surgical technology and industrial materials, the treatment of aortic diseases continues to develop in the direction of minimally invasive, rapid and efficient.
Doctors can properly "divert" the blood flow by piercing the thigh and placing a stent in the aorta to avoid the impact on the aneurysm or ruptured dissection, and achieve a good therapeutic effect. Some operations even require only local anesthesia.
This academic seminar invited more than ten domestic experts to discuss the new progress in the treatment of aortic diseases, and conducted cutting-edge technical training and difficult case discussions in the form of a conference salon.
The reporter learned at the meeting that with the development of surgical technology and industrial materials, the current treatment of aortic diseases continues to develop in the direction of minimally invasive, rapid and efficient.
