The longest high-speed rail tunnel in the Three Gorges Reservoir Area is connected - chinanews.com
2020-07-26 17: 34: 48 Source: China News Network Author: Chen Haifeng Editor: Chen Haifeng
The picture shows the construction site of the Small Three Gorges Tunnel.
China Railway Chengdu Bureau Group
Chinanews.com, Chongqing, July 26 (Reporter Han Lu) The reporter learned from China Railway Chengdu Bureau Group Co., Ltd. on the 26th that the Zhengwan High-speed Railway Small Three Gorges Tunnel with a total length of about 18.9 kilometers was fully connected on the same day.
It is understood that the Small Three Gorges Tunnel is not only the longest high-speed rail tunnel within the Three Gorges Reservoir area, but also the longest single-hole double-track high-speed rail tunnel with a design speed of 350 kilometers per hour among the projects currently under construction in China.
The Zhengwan high-speed railway is located in the three provinces and cities of Henan, Hubei, and Chongqing. It is connected to the Beijing-Guangzhou and Xulan high-speed rail in the north of Zhengzhou, and the Chongqing-Chongqing high-speed railway in the south of Wanzhou. It is an important part of my country's "eight vertical and eight horizontal" high-speed railway network along the river channel and the Hunan channel.
The Zhengwan High-speed Railway Small Three Gorges Tunnel was completed on the 26th.
The picture shows the passage through the scene.
The Zhengwan high-speed railway starts in Zhengzhou City, Henan Province, and runs southwest through Pingdingshan City, Nanyang City, and Xiangyang City, Hubei Province to Wanzhou District, Chongqing City. The new line is about 818 kilometers long, with a design speed of 350 kilometers per hour, and about 184 kilometers in Chongqing.
Among them, the Zhengzhou-Xiangyang section has been opened for operation in advance on December 1, 2019, and the Chongqing section is stepping up construction.
The Small Three Gorges Tunnel, which was fully connected on the 26th, is a full-line control project of the Zhengwan High-speed Railway. The project is located at the junction of Fengjie County and Wushan County, Chongqing City, with a total length of about 18.9 kilometers and a maximum buried depth of 890 meters.
Construction of the tunnel began in February 2017, and the entire line was opened on July 26, 2020.
According to Wang Guojun, head of the design of the Zhengwan High-speed Railway Tunnel, China Railway Second Engineering Group Co., Ltd., the survey and design party, the location of the Small Three Gorges Tunnel is very complex in topographic and geological conditions, facing risks such as karst, mud inrush, and large deformation of soft rock. It is a high-risk tunnel of Class I, and the tunnel design and construction are extremely difficult.
"During the construction of the project, we used geological survey methods, geophysical methods, and advanced drilling methods to advance geological forecasting, and adopted special design plans for more than 30 caves of various types. For example, a 24-meter-long bridge was designed and built, spanning large caves with a longitudinal length of more than 10 meters and a depth of more than 55 meters in the tunnel to avoid tunnel settlement", Wang Guojun said.
According to the China Railway Tunnel Bureau of the construction party, during the construction of the tunnel, a combination of dredging and blocking was adopted. Through the construction of horizontal tunnels, grouting and water blocking, the strengthening of tunnel structure support and the construction of sewage treatment stations, it not only ensured the orderly progress of the project, but also avoided the damage of construction drainage to the water body of the Small Three Gorges Scenic Area. At the same time, it successfully overcame construction difficulties such as the 7-kilometer-long soft rock large deformation and other bad geology, and the daily maximum water inrush of 157,000 cubic meters.
After the full line of Zhengwan High-speed Railway is completed and opened to traffic, it will become a new convenient and fast passenger passage from southwestern China to the Central Plains, North China, and Northeast China. It is of great significance to improve the capacity and quality of the northeast railway passage in southwestern China, improve the regional road network layout, accelerate the development of tourism resources and urbanization along the route, promote coordinated regional development, and promote the implementation of the western development strategy.
