Economic Daily, China Economic Network Reporter Lin firecan
In the first half of this year, in the face of the impact of COVID-19, my country coordinated efforts to promote epidemic prevention and control and economic and social development. The epidemic prevention and control situation has continued to improve, the economy has steadily recovered, and the employment and price performance that is closely related to the people's livelihood has been generally stable. The Chinese economy has handed over a report card of economic performance with temperature.
In the first two months of this year, the surveyed unemployment rate increased.
Especially in February, the production and operation activities of many enterprises were basically in a state of suspension of work and production, and the employment demand of enterprises was reduced, recruitment was delayed or cancelled, and the surveyed unemployment rate in cities and towns increased.
With the gradual improvement of the epidemic prevention and control situation, the production and life order of the whole society has been continuously restored.
The Party Central Committee adheres to the general tone of steady progress, further strengthens the macro-policy countermeasure, comprehensively strengthens the employment priority policy, and actively promotes the work of assisting enterprises to stabilize and expand employment.
My country has stepped up its policies to stabilize jobs, played a combination of the policy of "relief, delay and return", phased reduction and exemption of three social insurance unit contributions, allowed deferred payment of social insurance premiums, expanded the return of unemployment insurance for small, medium and micro enterprises, and benefited from the training policy for workers, and provided absorption subsidies and trainee subsidies for enterprises to absorb the employment of key groups.
With the implementation of various employment stabilization policies, the demand for employment by enterprises has steadily rebounded, the employment situation has gradually improved, and the surveyed unemployment rate in cities and towns has gradually decreased. In June, the surveyed unemployment rate was 5.7%.
Zhang Yi, director of the Population and Employment Statistics Division of the National Bureau of Statistics, said that in the second quarter, various employment policies continued to be effective. The labor force who withdrew due to the impact of the epidemic in the early stage returned one after another. The urban labor participation rate in June increased by about 10 percentage points from February, close to the level of the same period last year.
Data show that the total urban employment in June increased by more than 19% compared with February, and most industries reached the pre-epidemic level; the average weekly working hours of corporate employees reached 46.8 hours, an increase of 6.6 hours over February and slightly higher than January by 0.1 hours.
Prices are also related to thousands of households.
In January this year, the CPI rose by 5.4% year-on-year, setting a new high in many years.
Entering February, although the year-on-year increase in CPI fell slightly, it was still in the "5 range".
The year-on-year increase in CPI is at a high level, due to factors driving consumer demand before the Spring Festival, as well as factors such as the wrong month of the Spring Festival and a low year-on-year base.
However, the impact of COVID-19 on prices is particularly obvious.
Affected by the prevention and control of the epidemic, in January and February, there were delays in logistics, untimely supply of materials, and increased transportation costs of materials across the country. In addition, some citizens hoarded and rushed to buy, and the prices of some daily necessities increased significantly.
In response to the disturbance caused by the epidemic prevention and control to the price situation, relevant departments have included important living materials in the scope of emergency transportation guarantee to ensure smooth transportation of materials.
Under the action of a series of policy measures, the market supply of vegetables and fruits has been strongly guaranteed.
