Since March, pork prices have continued to decline, and in May the year-on-year increase in food prices fell to 10.6%; in June, affected by factors such as the slowdown in the exit of live pigs, reduced imports, and the rebound in group consumer demand, pork prices rose slightly.
The seasonal variation of fresh vegetable prices is obvious, with an average increase of 3.4% in the first half of the year.
Affected by the high comparison base in the same period last year, the price of fresh fruits continued to decline year-on-year, with an average drop of 13.3% in the first half of the year.
The basic lives of the masses are effectively guaranteed, and the overall economic and social situation remains stable and orderly.
With the gradual recovery of transportation and logistics, various places have increased their efforts to ensure supply, and the market supply and demand situation has improved.
Starting in March, the CPI fell for four consecutive months, and the year-on-year increase also fell from 4.3% in March to 2.5% in June, and the overall price level returned to stability.
In the second half of the year, prices in my country will continue to remain at a moderate level, with little overall inflationary pressure, but it is still necessary to promote the restoration of production and living order under the premise of normalizing epidemic prevention and control.
Effectively respond to natural disasters such as floods and droughts in major agricultural production areas such as grain, fruits and vegetables, strengthen market supervision, and resolutely crack down on disturbing market order such as hoarding and price hikes.
