The "Lancet" published an article praising China's anti-epidemic efforts to encourage countries to learn from experience - chinanews.com
The Lancet magazine published an article on the 25th that China, as a country with a population of 1.4 billion and a size similar to that of Europe or the United States, has effectively controlled COVID-19 at this stage, and there has been no large-scale spread, which has largely controlled the domestic epidemic.
The article stated that in the past ten years, China has invested a lot in domestic research and public health construction, which makes China's preparation for COVID-19 much better than that of severe acute respiratory syndrome (SARS) that year.
The author said that when the SARS outbreak broke out in 2002, China was initially ill-prepared, especially the pathogen could not be identified.
When COVID-19 was discovered in December 2019, Chinese scientists were soon able to identify the type of virus and shared genome sequencing data with the international community on January 11, 2020.
By the end of January, doctors from mainland China and Hong Kong clarified the clinical characteristics of the virus and warned the world about the threat of COVID-19 through research papers published in The Lancet.
China has also been at the forefront of vaccine research. When the country declared a state of emergency, through close domestic cooperation, such research was carried out very quickly and strictly. In May and July, the results of the early trials of COVID-19 vaccine developed by China were announced in The Lancet.
China's experience shows that it is very important to invest in national health and research systems to effectively improve laboratory capabilities.
This is the basis for the country to respond quickly and effectively to health emergencies and global health security.
Other countries, especially low-income and middle-income countries, are very worthy of reference and learning.
In addition, China's experience has proved that on the basis of strong research, there must be a strong high-level and decisive scientific basis to make correct decisions, so that COVID-19 can be effectively controlled.
The article emphasizes that the government and its leaders must respect science, understand the value of science, and act on it in the most beneficial way for society.
In the early stage of the outbreak, the National Health and Construction Commission of China dispatched three groups of infectious disease experts to Wuhan to investigate the risk and spread of COVID-19. Their suggestions provided the basis for the decision to "close the city" in Wuhan on January 23; when some experts raised the necessity and urgency of building a square cabin hospital, the government quickly made a decision and implemented it quickly; at the same time, the extensive participation of the community and the masses also made the epidemic quickly and effectively controlled.
The article finally emphasizes that in response to global health emergencies, countries need to strengthen global cooperation and jointly respond.
