Dapeng's director "Good luck" was shortlisted for the Golden Goblet Award - Xinhuanet
On July 18, the 23rd Shanghai International Film Festival announced the official list of films selected for the Golden Goblet Award.
Director Dapeng's first realistic film, "Good luck", was successfully shortlisted for the Golden Goblet Award of the Shanghai Film Festival, and the film officially released its first poster.
Poster view
The film "Good luck" is Dapeng's first realistic work, and it is also his second bond with the Golden Goblet Award.
The film tells a story: A comedy director had a whim and returned to his hometown in the northeastern countryside, hoping to make a literary and artistic film for the family during the New Year. As a result, he encountered a series of accidents.
The family members gathered for making the movie completed the final party.
In the movie poster released today, a member of this family-" Three Uncle "Wang Jixiang is sitting in the middle of the picture smoking a cigarette. The background is the black land of the Northeast dressed in silver, and the foreground is the red lantern that the Chinese people must hang during the New Year.
The red lanterns, which symbolize joy and reunion, form a huge contrast with the desolate Wang Jixiang, which also seems to reveal the complexity and entanglement in this extended family relationship.
It is reported that in the film, except for the daughter of "Three Uncle" Wang Jixiang, who is played by actor Liu Lu, the rest of the roles are completed by the real director's family. The experimental audio-visual style of the film breaks the boundary between drama and reality, and brings the audience a brand-new immersive viewing experience.
